%python
import os
import time
import matplotlib as mpl
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.cbook as cbook


def plot(in_learn, in_nolearn, week):
    data = np.loadtxt(in_learn, delimiter=',', skiprows=0)
    data2 = np.loadtxt(in_nolearn, delimiter=',', skiprows=0)
    day = data[:,0]
    inv = data[:,1]
    nDCG = data[:,2]
    hit = data[:,3]
    day2 = data2[:,0]
    inv2 = data2[:,1]
    nDCG2 = data2[:,2]
    hit2 = data2[:,3]
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))
    ax = fig.add_subplot(221)
    ax2 = fig.add_subplot(222)
    
    ax.set_ylabel('nDCG')
    ax2.set_ylabel('hit')
    
    fig.subplots_adjust(right=0.75)
    
    ax2.set_frame_on(True)
    ax2.patch.set_visible(False)
    
    for i in range(0, min(len(day), len(day2))):
        nDCG2[i] = nDCG2[i] * inv2[i] / inv[i]
        hit2[i] = hit2[i] * inv2[i] / inv[i]
    
    ax.plot(day, nDCG, marker='o', color="Red", label="item model")
    ax.plot(day2, nDCG2, marker='o', color="Magenta", label="no item model")
    ax.tick_params(axis='y', colors="Red")
    
    ax2.plot(day, hit, marker='o', color="Blue", label="item model")
    ax2.plot(day2, hit2, marker='o', color="Cyan", label="no item model")
    ax2.tick_params(axis='y', colors="Blue")
    
    ax.set_xlabel('Day (Week '+str(week)+')')
    ax2.set_xlabel('Day (Week '+str(week)+')')
    
    ax.legend()
    ax2.legend()
    ax.grid()
    ax2.grid
    plt.ylim(0,0.15)
    plt.show()
